This week, Kenya marks exactly one year since going to the ballot in 2017,Â in the nation's biggest election since independence. While the country now seems to have moved on from the heavily contested and controversial polls, many Kenyans are still trying to come to terms with the loss of their kin and how it happened following the violence witnessed after the elections. KTN news anchor and political affairs reporter Akisa Wandera has the first of a three?part series, The price of democracy.  